\begin{cor*}
Any finite dimensional, uniformly smooth metric space $(X,d)$ of
non-negative curvature in the sense of Gromov and non-trivial boundary
property admits closed convex set $S$ such that $\partial_{g}S=\varnothing$.
We call $S$ a soul of $X$.
\end{cor*}
Note that the construction of the deformation retracts also work inside
