summarize the results above as follows. 
\begin{thm}
Assume $(X,d)$ is uniformly smooth, strong non-negatively curved
in the sense of Gromov and has strict convexity radius locally bounded
away from zero. Then there is a strong deformation retract onto a
closed convex set $S$ with $\partial_{g}S=\varnothing$.
\end{thm}
